Q_DESC:
Bonk considers Jade to be a very close friend of his. But, he ends up having some misunderstanding with him a lot of times, because Jade's English isn't perfect, and Bonk sucks at the language Jade speaks. So, he's in a fix - since he knows that Jade has got magical powers, he asks him to help so as to clear all the issues they end up having with their friendship.

Now, Jade can only focus at one task, so to fix these language issues he comes up with a magical way out, but someone needs to do the rest of it; this is where Bonk has asked for your help.

Bonk says a word, and then Jade says another word. If any sub-string of the word said by Jade is a sub-string of the word said by Little Jhool, the output should be "YES", else "NO". (Without the quotes.)

Input:
First line contains number of test case T. Each test case contains two strings *Text ( Said by Bonk ) * and Pattern (Said by Jade ).Both strings contains only lowercase alphabets ['a'-'z'].

Output:
For each test case print YES if any sub-string of Pattern is sub-string of Text else print NO.

Constraints: 
1<=T<=5
1<=|Text|<=100000
1<=|Pattern|<=100000
